    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Hebrews",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 3,
        "summary": "Christ is the Apostle and High Priest of our profession\u2014Jesus, being the Son, is more than a servant\u2014Now is the time and the day of our salvation.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Wherefore, holy brethren, partakers of the heavenly calling, consider the Apostle and High Priest of our profession, Christ Jesus;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Meditation.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Messenger of the Covenant.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 81
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0High Priest, Melchizedek Priesthood.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 97
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Who was faithful to him that appointed him, as also Moses was faithful in all his house.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For this man was counted worthy of more glory than Moses, inasmuch as he who hath builded the house hath more honour than the house.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 12
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For every house is builded by some man; but he that built all things is God.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And Moses verily was faithful in all his house, as a servant, for a testimony of those things which were to be spoken after;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Servant.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But Christ as a son over his own house; whose house are we, if we hold fast the confidence and the rejoicing of the hope firm unto the end.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Church.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Pet. 2:5 (4\u20138).",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore (as the Holy Ghost saith, To day if ye will hear his voice,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Heb. 10:15.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 95:7 (7\u201311).",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Harden not your hearts, as in the provocation, in the day of temptation in the wilderness:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hardheartedness.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Num. 14:23 (2\u201323); Jacob 1:7 (7\u20138); Alma 12:36.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When your fathers tempted me, proved me, and saw my works forty years.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Test.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore I was grieved with that generation, and said, They do alway err in their heart; and they have not known my ways.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 30:12 (11\u201314).",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "So I sware in my wrath, They shall not enter into my rest.)",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 95:11.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 84:24. TG\u00a0God, Presence of; God, Privilege of Seeing; Rest.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 57
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Take heed, brethren, lest there be in any of you an evil heart of unbelief, in departing from the living God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 6:5; Matt. 15:19; Hel. 12:4.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 62
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Stiffnecked.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0apostatizing, withdrawing from. TG\u00a0Apostasy of Individuals.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But exhort one another daily, while it is called To day; lest any of you be hardened through the deceitfulness of sin.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 34:39; D&C 38:23. TG\u00a0Chastening.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 45:6.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 55
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For we are made partakers of Christ, if we hold the beginning of our confidence steadfast unto the end;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Perseverance; Steadfastness.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "While it is said, To day if ye will hear his voice, harden not your hearts, as in the provocation.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Contrite Heart.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 58
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Provoking.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 97
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For some, when they had heard, did provoke: howbeit not all that came out of Egypt by Moses.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But with whom was he grieved forty years? was it not with them that had sinned, whose carcases fell in the wilderness?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Num. 14:29 (29, 37); 1\u00a0Cor. 10:5 (2\u20137).",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And to whom sware he that they should not enter into his rest, but to them that believed not?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "So we see that they could not enter in because of unbelief.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Unbelief.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}